Fake News Detector (Python + Google Colab)

A simple Fake News Detection System built using TF-IDF vectorization and PassiveAggressiveClassifier.
This project classifies news headlines as REAL or FAKE based on textual patterns.


---

Features

Works entirely in Google Colab (no computer required)

Uses TF-IDF to extract text features

Compares two models:

PassiveAggressiveClassifier

LogisticRegression


Displays accuracy, classification report, confusion matrix

Supports testing custom news sentences

Saves trained model files (.joblib)



---

Tech Stack

Python 3

Scikit-Learn

Pandas, NumPy

Matplotlib & Seaborn

Google Colab (runtime environment)



